arXiv:2410.06951v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We investigate the exclusive rare semileptonic decays: $B(B_c)	o K(D_{(s)})l ar{l}/\Sigma
u_l ar{
u_l}$ ($l=\mu, 	au$) in the framework of relativistic independent quark (RIQ) model based on an average flavor independent confining potential in equally mixed scalar-vector harmonic form. The invariant weak form factors, parametrising the matrix elements between participating meson states are calculated in the parent meson rest frame. The momentum transfer dependence of the form factors is reliably determined in the whole accessible kinematical range: $q^2_{min}\leq 0\leq q^2_{max}$. Our predicted branching fractions for $B	o K\mu^+\mu^-/	au^+	au^-(\Sigma
u_l ar{
u_l})$, $B_c	o D(D_s)\mu^+\mu^-$, $B_c	o D(D_s)	au^+	au^-$ and $B_c	o D(D_s)\Sigma
u_l ar{
u_l}$, obtained in order of $10^{-7}(10^{-6})$, $10^{-9}(10^{-7})$, $10^{-9}(10^{-8})$ and $10^{-8}(10^{-7})$, respectively are in reasonable agreement with other Standard Model predictions and Lattice QCD results. The averaged values of the lepton polarization asymmetries for decay modes are obtained as $\langle P_L(B	o K\mu^+\mu^-)angle$=-0.97, $\langle P_L(B_c	o D_{(s)}\mu^+\mu^-)angle$=-0.972, $\langle P_L(B	o K	au^+	au^-)angle$=-0.224, $\langle P_L(B_c	o D	au^+	au^-)angle$=-0.275 and $\langle P_L(B_c	o D_s	au^+	au^-)angle$=-0.194.
